  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Federal contract obligations for NAICS 541380 (Testing Laboratories) stand at $322M for FY2026 to date. Award activity this fiscal year includes 2,489 awards with an average award size of $129K, and obligations fell 43.9% year over year. Year-to-year fiscal totals show a peak at $671M in FY24 and a decline to $574M in FY25 before the current FY26 total of $322M. The Department of Defense accounts for the largest share of FY2026 to date buying at $152M, followed by the Department of Veterans Affairs at $42.6M and the Department of Agriculture at $27.5M. Vendor concentration is notable: the top supplier, MERRICK & COMPANY, received $25.2M while AGILE DEFENSE, LLC received $24M and RAYTHEON COMPANY received $21.2M. These figures reflect partial-year obligations for FY2026 and represent the current federal market position for testing laboratory services without projecting future activity.",
