        "body": "Obligations fell 43.9% year over year to $322M in FY2026 to date. Fiscal-year totals show $502M in FY21, $575M in FY22, $619M in FY23, $671M in FY24, and $574M in FY25, followed by $322M in FY26."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies and contractors are the largest buyers and suppliers in FY2026 to date?",
        "body": "The Department of Defense is the largest buyer with $152M in obligations, followed by the Department of Veterans Affairs at $42.6M and the Department of Agriculture at $27.5M. Leading vendors by obligations are MERRICK & COMPANY at $25.2M, AGILE DEFENSE, LLC at $24M, and RAYTHEON COMPANY at $21.2M."
      }
